name: Unidentified_landspeeder_driver
content:
A human male landspeeder driver drove around Pantora at the beginning of the Imperial Era. When the bounty hunter Fennec Shand and the child clone, Omega, dropped onto a hovertruck, a chase then occured between Shand and Hunter. During the chase, Omega pulled the dump lever on the hovertruck, causing the bed to rise. This then caused Shand to fall onto a ComfortRide Passenger Airspeeder that this human was driving. Unbeknownst that Shand was still holding on to the airspeeder, the assassin knocked out the driver as she tossed him out of the vehicle.
The human landspeeder driver first appeared in "Cornered," the fourth episode of the first season of Star Wars: The Bad Batch. He was voiced by Taran Killam.
